    <briefdescription>
<para>This class implements the <ref refid="class_hd_embree_primvar_sampler" kindref="compound">HdEmbreePrimvarSampler</ref> interface for primvars on triangle meshes with &quot;face-varying&quot; interpolation modes. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This means that each vertex of each face gets its own buffer item: vertex 0 as part of face 0 might have value 1.0f, but vertex 0 as part of face 1 might have value 2.0f. The primvar&apos;s memory layout is grouped by face, with one item per vertex.</para>
<para>Concretely, a cube with 8 vertices would have 24 items (6 faces * 4 vertices) in a face-varying primvar, and the index of the item for face 2, vertex 3, would be (2 * 4 + 3) = 11.</para>
<para>Face-varying primvars are provided to the sampler un-triangulated, but the size of the buffer is tied to the size of the topology, so this class triangulates the input buffer before sampling. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
